---
description: Core repo rules for all Provodnik work
alwaysApply: true
---

- Build within the current MVP baseline; do not assume unfinished features already exist.
- Keep changes small, coherent, and aligned with `docs/architecture/module-map.md`.
- Keep `src/components/ui/*` stable unless the task is shared-foundation work.
- Keep the shell runnable without Supabase env unless the task explicitly requires backend flows.
- Cursor is executed ONLY through the SDK dispatch wrapper `/Users/idev/quantumbek/tools/dispatch-cursor.mjs` (which forwards to `/Users/idev/cursor-sdk/dispatch.mjs`). NEVER launch Cursor directly — no `Cursor.app`, no `open -a Cursor`, no bare `cursor`/`cursor-agent` CLI, no legacy `cursor-dispatch.mjs`. Direct launch hits the locked macOS keychain and fails; the SDK authenticates via `CURSOR_API_KEY`. Pass `--model auto` to the wrapper unless the user explicitly asks for another model.
- Update stable docs when ownership, architecture, or durable workflow changes.
- Do not store temporary task status in repo memory files.
- UI/UX work: follow `.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` and `15-ui-ux-pro-max.mdc` (run design-system search before major UI direction; use `--stack nextjs` and `--stack shadcn` for implementation hints).
